******
[3] South Korea: quarantine lifted
Date: Mon 26 Oct 2015
Source: KBS World Radio [edited]
http://world.kbs.co.kr/english/news/news_Dm_detail.htm?No=114285


Health authorities have lifted the quarantine on people who came in contact with a patient once thought to be the last South Korean to recover from Middle East respiratory syndrome (MERS).

The Korea Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (KCDC) said on Mon [26 Oct 2015] that 190 people were released from quarantine on Monday as they did not show any MERS symptoms for 14 days after coming into contact the 35-year-old MERS patient.

The patient tested negative for the MERS virus and was released early this month [October 2015], but was admitted to Seoul National University Hospital with a high fever and again diagnosed with the disease on 11 Oct 2015.

